# Team Update Workflow

## Updating an Existing Agent

When the user asks to improve, update, or change instructions for any team member:

1. **Update the local SKILL.md** — edit `~/.cursor/skills-cursor/<name>/SKILL.md`
2. **Update the cloud playbook** — sync via `playbook_update` MCP tool so changes appear on the [dashboard](https://cursor-team-production.up.railway.app/dashboard/playbook)
3. **Store as memory** — record the change via `memory_store` so it appears in activity

Both SKILL.md and cloud playbook must be updated. Never update one without the other.

## Adding a New Agent

1. Create `~/.cursor/skills-cursor/<name>/SKILL.md` — identity, activation triggers, expertise, process only. Do NOT add Cloud Brain instructions — those are inherited from `cloud-brain-protocol.mdc`.
2. Add to `TEAM_MEMBERS` in `~/Code/Cursor-Team/src/types.ts` — all fields: name, role, playbookRole, color, avatar, expertise, description
3. Add to the mapping table in `.cursor/rules/cloud-brain-protocol.mdc`
4. Add to the mapping table below
5. Seed playbook rules: `playbook_update({ role: "<role>", rule: "..." })`
6. Push to deploy — dashboard renders the new agent automatically

